Reasoning: The paper deals with the design and construction of Space-Time Block Codes (STBCs) for multiple antennas, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the complexity of decoding these codes, which could be relevant to Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper proposes a new construction scheme for STBCs, which could be considered as a contribution to Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed codes through simulations, which could be relevant to Multimedia (cs.MM).
